WEBVTT

00:05.918 --> 00:07.659
["The Good Life"
by Tony Bennett playing]

00:12.490 --> 00:14.318
♪ Oh

00:14.492 --> 00:18.888
♪ The good life ♪

00:19.062 --> 00:20.890
♪ Full of fun ♪

00:21.064 --> 00:22.674
♪ Seems to be ♪

00:22.848 --> 00:25.242
♪ The ideal ♪

00:29.507 --> 00:32.858
♪ Mmm, the good life

00:33.033 --> 00:34.904
♪ Lets you hide ♪

00:35.078 --> 00:37.602
♪ All the sadness you feel... ♪

00:37.776 --> 00:39.561
DARNELL:
You ready, babe?

00:43.043 --> 00:45.654
♪ You won't really...

00:45.828 --> 00:47.090
Ready.

00:47.264 --> 00:50.093
♪ Fall in love ♪

00:50.267 --> 00:54.054
♪ For you can't take
the chance ♪

00:56.708 --> 00:58.362
♪ So please

00:58.536 --> 01:00.712
♪ Be honest ♪

01:00.886 --> 01:04.107
♪ With yourself ♪

01:04.281 --> 01:08.285
♪ Don't try to fake romance ♪

01:10.461 --> 01:14.552
♪ It's the good life

01:14.726 --> 01:17.207
♪ To be free... [elevator bell dings]

01:18.948 --> 01:20.863
[alarm ringing]

01:21.037 --> 01:23.083
[Murphy gasps]

01:24.345 --> 01:26.564
[crying]:
No, no...

01:26.738 --> 01:28.610
Please, no.

01:28.740 --> 01:31.439
[sobbing]:
No!

01:31.613 --> 01:34.094
No!

01:34.268 --> 01:35.834
Please...

01:35.965 --> 01:39.186
♪ Well, just wake up ♪

01:39.360 --> 01:42.972
♪ Kiss the good life ♪

01:43.146 --> 01:45.540
♪ Goodbye. No!

01:45.714 --> 01:48.325
[Darnell gasps]

01:48.499 --> 01:50.110
No!

01:53.374 --> 01:55.898
♪ [Murphy screams]

02:03.949 --> 02:04.776
GENE: Well, guys, now
that the whole Josh thing

02:04.950 --> 02:05.995
is off the table,

02:06.169 --> 02:07.388
we're back
to square zero.

02:07.562 --> 02:09.564
So, what?
We're just...

02:09.738 --> 02:11.609
We're supposed to go
back to trial? I...

02:11.783 --> 02:13.655
We know how that's
gonna end. I can't...

02:13.829 --> 02:15.657
We need to figure out
another game plan.

02:15.831 --> 02:16.962
Game plan?
We have nothing.

02:17.137 --> 02:18.877
Well, let's
figure it out.

02:19.051 --> 02:20.879
Hopefully, we still have
a little bit of time.

02:21.053 --> 02:22.881
I'm really sorry
about all this, Murphy.

02:25.101 --> 02:27.582
When I let Trey get away,
I didn't think...

02:27.756 --> 02:29.801
[sighs]

02:29.975 --> 02:31.151
Anyway, I'm sorry.

02:31.325 --> 02:33.457
It's fine. I mean,
let's just...

02:33.631 --> 02:34.676
Can we just
think, please?

02:34.850 --> 02:36.547
It actually isn't fine.Max...

02:36.678 --> 02:38.549
This should've been over. Done.

02:38.723 --> 02:40.682
But here we are.

02:40.856 --> 02:42.031
Glad Trey's having
a great day, though.

02:42.205 --> 02:44.381
I apologized.Cool, thanks.

02:44.555 --> 02:45.774
MURPHY:
You guys, my deal is done

02:45.904 --> 02:47.079
if we don't take down
the Bolt operation

02:47.254 --> 02:49.125
in the next,
like, day.
[sighs]

02:49.256 --> 02:51.214
So, I say we get a warrant
for the club.

02:51.388 --> 02:52.694
Get something there.

02:52.868 --> 02:54.913
It's clean. Trey knows
what he's doing.

02:55.087 --> 02:56.219
Everything
there's legit.

02:56.393 --> 02:58.874
MURPHY:
So, how are we gonna get him?

02:59.048 --> 03:00.919
I know y'all want Trey

03:01.093 --> 03:03.574
to go down, okay, and...

03:03.705 --> 03:05.315
and he will,

03:05.489 --> 03:07.012
but if you want
to stop Bolt, for real,

03:07.187 --> 03:09.580
I think we got to
bust them both

03:09.711 --> 03:11.930
at the same time.

03:12.104 --> 03:13.845
Trey and this
investor dude.

03:14.019 --> 03:15.847
Why at the same time?

03:16.021 --> 03:17.893
We can't risk them warning
each other. I mean,

03:18.067 --> 03:19.895
Trey can do this on his own,

03:20.069 --> 03:21.375
and so can this investor.

03:21.549 --> 03:22.854
I mean, he'll just
find another Trey.

03:23.028 --> 03:24.291
Both too smart.

03:26.031 --> 03:28.469
I thought Trey didn't know
who this guy was.

03:28.643 --> 03:31.298
Yeah, well, I'm pretty sure
he was lying.

03:31.472 --> 03:32.951
I can get it out of him.

03:33.125 --> 03:34.214
GENE:
And then what?

03:34.388 --> 03:35.693
I doubt there's
any dirt on this guy,

03:35.867 --> 03:36.868
whoever he is.

03:37.042 --> 03:37.652
MURPHY:
We-we get this investor

03:37.826 --> 03:39.088
to sell to us,

03:39.262 --> 03:42.526
we set up, like,
a sting or something.

03:42.700 --> 03:44.267
You think you can actually
get him to sell you drugs?

03:44.441 --> 03:45.877
Like a mountain of drugs?
Because that's

03:46.051 --> 03:47.314
what we would need.

03:47.488 --> 03:48.315
Yeah.

03:48.489 --> 03:49.751
Okay.

03:49.925 --> 03:52.971
You're gonna need money,
a lot of it,

03:53.145 --> 03:55.060
and I can't get it
from the department.

03:55.235 --> 03:56.061
We'll figure it out.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.847
[scoffs]
GENE: Uh,

03:58.977 --> 04:02.372
keep in mind, Sarah and myself
are officers of the law.

04:02.546 --> 04:04.505
We cannot be a party
to anything illegal.

04:04.679 --> 04:07.290
Okay. Okay,
then, uh,

04:07.464 --> 04:09.249
what if we set
everything up,

04:09.423 --> 04:10.772
and then you guys come in
and do the arrests

04:10.946 --> 04:12.426
after the deal's done?

04:12.600 --> 04:13.296
GENE:
We'll have to run it
by the chief first,

04:13.470 --> 04:14.515
but shouldn't be
a problem.

04:16.734 --> 04:17.909
We good with that?

04:18.083 --> 04:20.912
At this point, yeah, sure.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.350
MURPHY:
Okay, Darnell, you go figure
out who the investor is.

04:23.524 --> 04:25.352
Max and I will figure out
how to get the money.

04:25.526 --> 04:27.702
Then we'll...
wait for your call.

04:34.404 --> 04:37.146
So, remember how you got that
200 grand to bail me out?

04:37.320 --> 04:38.887
Wait, so you're a CI?Where did that
money come from?

04:39.061 --> 04:40.541
And everyone
knew but me?

04:40.715 --> 04:42.151
That's why you needed "space"?

04:42.325 --> 04:43.500
That's why you sent
me and Lesley away?

04:44.545 --> 04:46.024
Oh, my God.

04:46.198 --> 04:48.026
You know, she dragged me
to frickin' Anguilla.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.508
I'm sorry you were dragged
to Anguilla, Felix.

04:51.682 --> 04:52.509
FELIX:
It was horrible.

04:52.683 --> 04:53.771
I didn't sleep at all,

04:53.945 --> 04:55.643
I'm extremely sunburned,

04:55.817 --> 04:56.861
and then I was alone
the whole time because she met

04:57.035 --> 04:58.776
some girl, so...

04:58.950 --> 05:00.952
Well, where is Lesley?

05:01.126 --> 05:03.607
She's... had to "take a nap"

05:03.781 --> 05:05.348
when she heard
you were coming, so...

05:05.522 --> 05:07.916
Okay, well, I should
probably talk to her.

05:08.046 --> 05:09.570
I haven't really spoken
to her since...

05:09.744 --> 05:10.832
well, everything.

05:10.962 --> 05:11.963
Do you mind?

05:12.137 --> 05:14.183
Yeah, no. Should.Yeah?

05:15.967 --> 05:17.665
[sighs]

05:18.753 --> 05:21.321
[sighing]

05:23.366 --> 05:25.063
Anyway...
[sighs]

05:25.194 --> 05:26.717
Um, about the money,

05:26.848 --> 05:28.066
I need you to go back
to that family friend...

05:28.197 --> 05:29.503
What's that
on your finger?

05:29.633 --> 05:31.331
What?

05:35.596 --> 05:37.206
Um...

05:37.380 --> 05:40.862
Yeah. Max-Max and I are...

05:41.036 --> 05:43.299
are... getting married.
[chuckles]

05:44.431 --> 05:45.867
[scoffs softly]

05:52.134 --> 05:54.092
How's your nap?

05:55.877 --> 05:57.792
Wonderful.

06:00.969 --> 06:03.101
I'm really sorry

06:03.275 --> 06:05.321
about the way
everything went down.

06:06.931 --> 06:07.758
[sighs]

06:07.932 --> 06:09.630
You were...

06:09.804 --> 06:11.240
are...

06:11.414 --> 06:13.373
this incredible person, and...

06:13.547 --> 06:15.244
you didn't deserve this.

06:20.118 --> 06:22.817
It was always her,
wasn't it?

06:24.688 --> 06:26.603
Come on, just be honest
with me, you owe me that.

06:27.822 --> 06:28.997
Yeah.

06:29.127 --> 06:30.694
I can't help it.

06:32.653 --> 06:34.742
It was, it is,
it's always gonna be.

06:37.222 --> 06:39.616
It's my lot in life.

06:39.790 --> 06:41.444
[chuckles]

06:43.315 --> 06:45.709
You could've just told me that.

06:45.883 --> 06:47.581
Saved me some time.

06:49.800 --> 06:51.715
Just sort of realized it.

06:57.460 --> 06:59.375
I always knew.

07:01.333 --> 07:03.466
On some level. I just...

07:05.642 --> 07:07.078
I don't know.

07:11.866 --> 07:14.434
Heard you met someone
in Anguilla.

07:15.739 --> 07:17.654
Don't.

07:17.828 --> 07:19.961
We're not friends...

07:20.091 --> 07:21.179
yet.

07:22.442 --> 07:23.704
Yet?

07:30.058 --> 07:31.276
[sniffles]

07:31.451 --> 07:33.714
Will you
say something?

07:33.888 --> 07:35.716
Anything?

07:35.890 --> 07:36.891
[sighs]

07:38.719 --> 07:40.677
Felix? [laughs]

07:40.851 --> 07:42.462
I mean...

07:44.159 --> 07:46.727
I've always wanted you
to be happy, Murphy, and...

07:47.771 --> 07:49.469
[exhales]

07:49.643 --> 07:51.209
...you've never
looked happier, so...

07:51.340 --> 07:52.907
[laughs]

07:53.081 --> 07:54.909
Congratulations.

07:55.083 --> 07:56.476
Thank you.

07:59.043 --> 08:01.089
But I swear to God I will murder
you if you ask me to be, like,

08:01.219 --> 08:03.308
your maid of honor
or something.
[laughing]

08:03.439 --> 08:05.920
FELIX:Well, anyway, I don't want to
see you get married in prison,

08:06.094 --> 08:07.487
so of course
I'll help you.

08:07.661 --> 08:08.488
Hey, Murphy.

08:12.013 --> 08:13.318
Hi.

08:15.582 --> 08:17.584
You guys want
something to drink?

08:18.933 --> 08:20.717
Oh, sure.
Thank you.

08:20.891 --> 08:21.849
[sniffles]

08:23.111 --> 08:25.330
Um...

08:25.505 --> 08:27.463
W... With the money?

08:28.769 --> 08:30.771
Um...

08:30.901 --> 08:32.686
You remember Jimmy McKay?[doorbell rings]

08:32.860 --> 08:34.905
FELIX:
I actually got the money
from his niece.

08:35.079 --> 08:36.341
I think she has a crush on me.MURPHY: Yeah.

08:36.472 --> 08:37.734
Well, maybe we can use that.

08:39.344 --> 08:40.389
Hey.

08:40.563 --> 08:41.608
Hey.

08:43.305 --> 08:44.654
Come in.
[chuckles]

08:52.227 --> 08:54.316
So, now you
want me to steal

08:54.490 --> 08:57.188
even more cash
from my uncle?

08:57.362 --> 08:59.408
Yes. Please?
[chuckles]

09:03.412 --> 09:04.674
Look, I-I wouldn't ask you

09:04.848 --> 09:06.807
unless it was, like,
a real emergency.

09:09.374 --> 09:11.072
What's the emergency?

09:11.202 --> 09:13.509
Um...

09:13.683 --> 09:15.642
I can't tell you.
[chuckles]

09:17.731 --> 09:19.428
What about your sister?
She's rich.

09:19.602 --> 09:22.300
Yeah, for reasons
that are way too long

09:22.474 --> 09:24.215
and boring, uh, to explain,

09:24.389 --> 09:26.174
my sister is not gonna give
one red cent

09:26.304 --> 09:28.132
to this mission.

09:28.306 --> 09:29.569
Mission?

09:31.527 --> 09:32.920
[chuckles]

09:34.791 --> 09:36.750
Seriously...

09:39.274 --> 09:41.406
...who are you
these days?

09:41.581 --> 09:43.147
[chuckles]

09:43.321 --> 09:45.672
I don't know.
[laughs]

09:56.813 --> 09:58.598
[both panting]

10:00.469 --> 10:01.905
[sighs]
[exhales]

10:02.079 --> 10:04.429
[laughs]

10:04.604 --> 10:06.214
[sighs]

10:06.388 --> 10:07.955
I'll get you the money.

10:09.652 --> 10:11.741
I feel a little dirty.[chuckles]

10:11.915 --> 10:13.438
Oh, you're more than
a little dirty.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.223
[both laugh]

10:21.142 --> 10:22.709
Seriously?
You're the one who
was working with the cops.

10:22.883 --> 10:24.624
Was, dude.
Come on.

10:26.321 --> 10:28.192
He's clean.Good.

10:29.890 --> 10:32.893
You're really letting
this whole thing

10:33.067 --> 10:34.590
go to your head,
you know that?

10:34.764 --> 10:35.939
You want a drink
or something?

10:36.113 --> 10:37.506
[sighs] Sure.

10:39.551 --> 10:41.031
So, uh, Nia's people,

10:41.162 --> 10:43.730
they're in.

10:43.904 --> 10:46.036
They're down to work
for you, man.

10:46.167 --> 10:47.821
Are you serious?

10:47.995 --> 10:49.518
I mean, they haven't had
anything to sell in months,

10:49.692 --> 10:51.476
and they definitely
heard of Bolt.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.740
Course they have.

10:53.914 --> 10:55.132
Everyone has.

10:55.306 --> 10:57.439
Pretty impressive,
I got to say.

10:57.613 --> 10:59.136
Mm.

10:59.310 --> 11:00.572
Pretty good
at my job.

11:00.747 --> 11:03.184
[laughing]
And so humble.

11:03.358 --> 11:04.707
Man, shut up.

11:07.362 --> 11:09.364
You know, I still

11:09.538 --> 11:11.627
can't believe you got
some rich dude

11:11.801 --> 11:13.150
to get his hands dirty
in something like this.

11:13.324 --> 11:14.848
He doesn't get his hands dirty.

11:15.022 --> 11:17.720
That's the whole point.
I've never even met the guy.

11:17.851 --> 11:19.983
So, what, you just talk
to him on the phone?

11:20.157 --> 11:22.638
No, not even that.

11:22.769 --> 11:23.987
He's an investor.

11:24.118 --> 11:25.902
That's it.

11:26.076 --> 11:27.338
Hmm.

11:27.512 --> 11:30.298
Man's probably never
even seen a Bolt pill.

11:30.428 --> 11:31.647
But you must've

11:31.821 --> 11:34.041
spoken to him
when he found you.

11:34.215 --> 11:36.130
Nah.

11:36.304 --> 11:38.045
♪

11:39.524 --> 11:41.309
[chuckles]

11:41.483 --> 11:44.399
I known you for too long.

11:44.573 --> 11:47.881
I know when you're lying at me.

11:48.055 --> 11:50.274
And I deserve to know who
I'm getting into business with.

11:50.448 --> 11:51.449
It's my ass now, too.

11:51.580 --> 11:53.364
Man, I'm not lying.

11:53.538 --> 11:54.714
All right?

11:56.237 --> 11:57.586
Okay, Trey.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.762
Then I'm out,

11:59.893 --> 12:02.460
and I'm taking
Nia's people with me.

12:02.591 --> 12:05.507
I can just start my own thing.

12:07.552 --> 12:08.902
Fine.

12:09.032 --> 12:12.035
♪ ♪

12:12.209 --> 12:14.516
Couple of months ago, I had
a chemist make the pill, right?

12:14.690 --> 12:16.953
Built a makeshift cookhouse,

12:17.127 --> 12:18.999
sold it to a couple people
I used to deal coke to,

12:19.173 --> 12:20.087
to test it out.

12:22.045 --> 12:25.135
One of them was this
really rich politician guy,

12:25.309 --> 12:26.746
Jimmy McKay.

12:30.097 --> 12:33.187
He liked it so much,
he told me he wanted to invest.

12:33.361 --> 12:35.189
He's an invisible partner.

12:36.320 --> 12:37.495
Hey, Uncle Jimmy.

12:37.669 --> 12:38.801
Oh, hey,
you going out?

12:38.932 --> 12:39.976
Yeah, just going
to see some friends.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.543
Well, have fun,kiddo.

12:47.244 --> 12:49.507
TREY:
This guy's really powerful.

12:49.681 --> 12:51.945
Like I said,
he's richer than God.

12:52.075 --> 12:53.729
Well...

12:53.860 --> 12:55.078
[sighs]

12:55.252 --> 12:56.993
I found out who
the guy is. [laughs]

12:57.167 --> 12:58.865
Who is it?

12:59.039 --> 13:01.606
Wait, you guys
actually got the money?

13:01.737 --> 13:03.217
Yeah. I'm basically
a prostitute now.

13:03.391 --> 13:05.175
What?
Who is it?

13:05.306 --> 13:06.829
It's this dude, uh,

13:06.960 --> 13:09.484
Jimmy McKay. Apparently,
he's this rich poli...

13:09.658 --> 13:12.269
Whoa, whoa, whoa, I'm sorry,
did you say Jimmy McKay?

13:12.443 --> 13:13.270
DARNELL:Yeah.

13:13.444 --> 13:14.750
You know who he is?

13:14.881 --> 13:17.187
FELIX:
Yeah, since I was,
like, two.

13:17.318 --> 13:20.060
And, ironically, the guy
who owns this money.

13:20.234 --> 13:21.061
DARNELL:
Oh.

13:21.235 --> 13:22.758
[sighs]

13:22.932 --> 13:24.542
Sorry, I-I-I'm having
trouble wrapping my head

13:24.716 --> 13:25.892
around the fact
that Jimmy McKay

13:26.066 --> 13:27.632
is tied into
the drug world.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.504
He's not.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.680
Apparently, he doesn't even
know anyone besides Trey.

13:31.854 --> 13:33.638
Trey just used to sell him coke,

13:33.769 --> 13:35.205
and Jimmy thought Bolt
was an easy way to make money.

13:35.336 --> 13:38.078
MAX:
Are we really gonna try
to buy drugs off this guy

13:38.252 --> 13:40.036
with his own
stolen money?

13:40.210 --> 13:42.473
No, because
I'm telling you

13:42.647 --> 13:44.345
Jimmy McKay's not gonna get
involved in a drug deal.

13:44.519 --> 13:45.389
He's like the most
powerful guy in Chicago.

13:45.563 --> 13:46.782
It's just-- He's not.

13:46.913 --> 13:48.088
Well, we'll have
to put him into

13:48.262 --> 13:49.089
a position where
he's forced to.

13:49.263 --> 13:50.481
How? Are you listening?

13:50.655 --> 13:52.353
The guy is squeaky clean.

13:52.527 --> 13:54.050
At least on paper.

13:54.224 --> 13:55.573
Yeah, Trey says
he stays far away.

13:55.704 --> 13:56.923
Wants no part of it.

13:57.097 --> 13:59.360
Then let's use that.

13:59.490 --> 14:00.927
MAX:
Meaning what?

14:01.101 --> 14:02.798
Meaning, he doesn't want
to get his hands dirty,

14:02.972 --> 14:03.930
then let's get
his hands dirty.

14:04.104 --> 14:06.280
That's not a terrible idea.

14:06.454 --> 14:08.804
You know, Trey says
he's taking a pretty big cut.

14:08.978 --> 14:10.110
I think I can work with that.

14:10.284 --> 14:12.677
I know how
to manipulate Trey.

14:15.028 --> 14:18.074
How much of a cut did you say
that Jimmy guy's getting again?

14:18.248 --> 14:20.555
20%.
[exhales]

14:20.729 --> 14:22.078
Told you it was steep.

14:22.252 --> 14:24.341
Steep? Bruh,
this is how much

14:24.515 --> 14:25.516
you're giving him
every month.

14:25.690 --> 14:27.823
It's obscene.

14:27.997 --> 14:30.130
You said yourself
he's richer than God.

14:30.304 --> 14:32.610
And you're the one
who set up this entire system,

14:32.784 --> 14:34.264
the labs, the laundering,
all of it.

14:34.395 --> 14:37.789
And this guy, who had nothing
to do with any of it,

14:37.964 --> 14:40.096
and already has all the money
in the world, is taking 20%?

14:40.270 --> 14:42.098
Come on.

14:43.273 --> 14:45.101
Yeah...

14:45.275 --> 14:46.624
But, I mean...

14:46.798 --> 14:49.410
I didn't have anything
when we started.

